## Unified Spec System (spec:*)

The feature specification and implementation workflow runs via the `spec-*` commands available globally:

| Command | Phase | Generated artifact |
|---|---|---|
| `/spec-constitution` | Pre-project | `.specs/memory/constitution.md` |
| `/spec-discover` | Phase 0 — Discover | `.specs/features/[f]/discovery.md` |
| `/spec-specify` | Phase 1 — Specify | `.specs/features/[f]/spec.md` |
| `/spec-design` | Phase 2 — Design | `.specs/features/[f]/design.md` |
| `/spec-tasks` | Phase 3 — Tasks | `.specs/features/[f]/tasks.md` |
| `/spec-implement` | Phase 4 — Implement+Validate | (analysis + validation) |
| `/spec-clarify` | Auxiliary | Resolves ambiguities in spec.md |
| `/spec-checklist` | Auxiliary | Feature acceptance criteria |
| `/spec-measure` | Phase 5 — Measure | `.specs/features/[f]/metrics.md` |

The complete behavior specification is in the `tlc-spec-driven` SKILL (in `~/.claude/SKILLS.md` or `~/.cursor/skills/tlc-spec-driven/SKILL.md`).
